Here is a look at key events in the student

pro-democracy movement that led to Sunday's assault by soldiers on protesters in Tiananmen Square: April 15 _ Former Communist Party chief Hu Yaobang dies.
April 27 _ More than 150,000 students, with wide support from people on the street, surge past police lines and fill Tiananmen Square, chanting slogans for democracy and freedom.
May 4 _ About 100,000 students and supporters march on Tiananmen Square to celebrate the 70th anniversary of China's first student movement.
May 28 _ About 80,000 people, many students from outside the capital, stage a demonstration, but unlike in past rallies few workers participate.
